Goodshuffle was founded in 2013 on the idea that rentals should be easy, fast, and accessible for everyone. One of our co-founders, Andrew Garcia, had a DJ business in college, and found that renting out equipment could be difficult and tedious. With his many years of experience as a Full Stack Developer, he knew he could change that. He partnered with Erik Dreyer, our other co-founder and UX extraordinaire, to build technology that made rentals easy.

Their first rental marketplace was targeted at peer-to-peer rentals, but after receiving so much demand for event rentals, they transitioned to gear their rental solutions to the industry from which Andrew originally came: events.

After interviewing a diverse array of event professionals, the pair realized they first must build a comprehensive software system in order to maximize the rental experience for both the vendors and the renters. They wanted to design a software program that not only did what event professionals needed it to do, but made it easy, fast and delightful along the way.

With renewed focus, the duo hit the ground running. They hired our Executive Vice President, Karen Gordon, who had years of experience growing companies in both the events and technology sectors. The trio launched their SaaS platform, Goodshuffle Pro, in 2017 as a beta program and officially premiered the software at a trade show in January 2018.

By 2019 the software was in 45 US states, Canada and Mexico. The company was crowned “Best Tech Startup in DC” and one of the “Coolest Places to Work” in 2020. Since then, our team, user base, and product have grown exponentially— and this is just the beginning.

We are a team of former event professionals and passionate technology professionals who are dedicated to creating the best solution for our industry. We believe that technology can, and should, be easy to use.

Blended Sense a media technology company out of Austin TX

In a time where digital communication is an essential part of daily business, we have 2 of the largest drivers of the US economy at risk. Small business owners and the Creative Freelancer.

Small Business owners do not have the time, resources, or the know-how to create and produce the digital assets they need to run their business and communicate with their target audience to thrive in today’s marketplace. 

Creative Freelancers are isolated and they struggle with customer service, accounting, and project management. This leaves 1 of 2 creatives struggling with cash flow. 

What we have built is a digital platform called Creative Intelligence. Our technology matches the right creative teams to the right projects and automates all of the pre-and post production logistics to de-risk the relationship between creative pros and small businesses. 

Our matches are hyper-local and create a recurring relationship between the two. We are one of the only companies that operate on a subscription basis for creative solutions to SMBS.
component--field-formatter 14: Media-Technology platform that connects small business owners with creative professionals on a subscription model
